This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring December 7, 2016, as National Pearl Harbor Remembrance Day. The proclamation highlights the attack on Pearl Harbor 75 years ago and the subsequent declaration of war by President Franklin D. Roosevelt. It pays tribute to the victims of the attack, honors the sacrifices made by those who served in the military, and emphasizes the importance of upholding the legacy of those who fought for the country. The proclamation calls on Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities and encourages the flying of the U.S. flag at half-staff.